<div class="column is-four-fifths is-offset-1 landing">
  <div class="box has-text-centered">
    <%= image_tag('logo.png', alt: "codnas q logo", class: 'logo') %>
    <h1 class="title has-margin-t-7">Conformational Diversity of Native State - Quaternary</h1>
    <p>
      CoDNaS-Q is a high-quality collection of homo-oligomeric conformers obtained from
      the <%= link_to('Protein Data Bank (PDB)', 'https://www.rcsb.org', target: "_blank") %>.
    </p>
    <p>
      It allows the exploration of conformational diversity and its determinants at the quaternary level,
      for a large number of proteins determined under different experimental conditions and from a wide variety of
      families and species.
    </p>
    <div>
      <%= form_tag(cluster_search_path, method: :get) do %>
        <div class="field has-addons is-grouped-centered column is-offset-3 is-three-fifths">
          <%= text_field_tag('query', '', class: 'input has-margin-r-7', placeholder: 'Search by...') %>
          <div class='select has-margin-r-7'>
            <%= select_tag('criteria', options_for_select(['All fields', 'PDB', 'Name', 'Organism'], 'All fields')) %>
          </div>
          <%= submit_tag('Search', class: 'button is-info') %>
        </div>
        <div class="has-margin-t-6">
          <span><small>Example entries: </small></span>
          <small><%= link_to('2vcq', cluster_show_path('2vcq')) %></small>
          <span><small> | </small></span><small><a href="/cluster/search?query=Hydrolase&amp;criteria=type">Hydrolase</a></small><span><small> | </small></span><small><a href="/cluster/search?query=Mus+musculus&amp;criteria=source">Mus
          musculus</a></small></div>
      <% end %>
    </div>
    <div class="has-margin-top-down" style="margin-top: 5rem">
      <p class="">browse by type of movement<small class="question-color" title="We can find three types of movements.
Tertiary deformations: where exist a predominance of local variations.
Rigid body: predominance of large displacements of subunits.
Mixed motions: they have the save (no) variation at both levels.
"> <%= fa_icon 'question-circle' %></small></p></div>

    <div class="columns is-0 is-centered">
      <!--      <div class="column">-->
      <div class="column is-one-quarter">      <%= link_to(
                                                     image_tag('mov_tert.gif', alt: 'tertiary deformation clusters'),
                                                     advanced_search_path(cluster_group: 'Tertiary Deformations'))
      %>
        <p class="has-text-danger is-size-5 has-text-weight-semibold">Tertiary Deformations</p>
      </div>
      <div class="column is-one-quarter">      <%= link_to(
                                                     image_tag('mov_mixed.gif', alt: 'mixed motion clusters'),
                                                     advanced_search_path(cluster_group: 'Mixed Motions'))
      %>
        <p class="has-text-success is-size-5 has-text-weight-semibold">Mixed Motions</p>
      </div>
      <div class="column is-one-quarter">      <%= link_to(
                                                     image_tag('mov_rigid.gif', alt: 'rigid body clusters'),
                                                     advanced_search_path(cluster_group: 'Rigid Body'))
      %>
        <p class="has-text-link is-size-5 has-text-weight-semibold">Rigid Body</p>
      </div>

      <!--    <div class="sample-gifs">-->
      <!--    </div>-->
      <!--      </div>-->
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

